flowRoot.flowPara: Go to the BEGIN block to start running your program.
Condition blocks: They evaluate an expression as true or false. They allow executing different code segments depending on whether the condition is true or false.
Direction blocks: Indicate where the program reading should follow.
Variable blocks: They can contain values that can be used and changed throughout a program.
Assignment blocks: Assign values to variables.
The END block marks the end of the program.
Code blocks: Set of instructions to be executed.
